The new Aarto declaration by president Cyril Ramaphosa has received the ire of many, and the support of some road users in South Africa. The Administrative Adjudication of Road Traffic Offences Act (Aarto) will be implemented by June next year. For some, this is still causing concern and there are many misconceptions about what changes the bill has in store for them. Eugene Herbert of MasterDrive provides some clarity for a better Aarto understanding.